00:44:50,918 --> 00:44:52,416
what are you
doing up here?

523
00:44:52,483 --> 00:44:54,980
seems like there was
this tiny jedediah smith

524
00:44:55,050 --> 00:44:56,646
standing on my shoulder,

525
00:44:56,715 --> 00:44:58,679
telling me to come
up here with you.

526
00:44:58,746 --> 00:45:00,145
i want to be like you, sir.

527
00:45:00,215 --> 00:45:02,079
much obliged, son.

528
00:45:02,146 --> 00:45:03,510
you do me
great honor.

529
00:45:03,578 --> 00:45:05,408
ah, but you see, sir,

530
00:45:05,476 --> 00:45:08,806
i'm just an ape
of jedediah smith.

531
00:45:08,876 --> 00:45:10,208
i want to be like you.

532
00:45:10,275 --> 00:45:11,706
i really want
to be like you,

533
00:45:11,773 --> 00:45:13,537
but there's a part of me
that i feel inside--

534
00:45:13,605 --> 00:45:15,270
i want to be back
down there with them.

535
00:45:15,338 --> 00:45:16,336
what does that make me?

536
00:45:16,403 --> 00:45:18,167
makes you
a human being.

537
00:45:18,237 --> 00:45:20,634
just like
the rest of us.

538
00:45:20,702 --> 00:45:23,465
are you tempted,
too, sir?

539
00:45:23,533 --> 00:45:25,464
come over here.
sit down, boy.

540
00:45:25,531 --> 00:45:26,429
come over here.

541
00:45:30,629 --> 00:45:32,526
jacob...

542
00:45:32,594 --> 00:45:36,091
we're as human
as the least of 'em
down there,

543
00:45:36,159 --> 00:45:38,090
but we're also
more than that.

544
00:45:40,323 --> 00:45:41,887
"as a man thinketh,
so he is. "

545
00:45:41,956 --> 00:45:43,554
what do you
think you are?

546
00:45:46,519 --> 00:45:48,118
the lord fashioned us

547
00:45:48,186 --> 00:45:49,782
a little above
the beast,

548
00:45:49,851 --> 00:45:51,848
a little below
the angels,

549
00:45:51,917 --> 00:45:54,613
but he gave us
the choice.

550
00:45:54,680 --> 00:45:56,611
and it's great, son.

551
00:46:00,012 --> 00:46:01,576
some of these men,
they come west,

552
00:46:01,644 --> 00:46:03,208
they lose
their souls.

553
00:46:05,943 --> 00:46:07,808
west is a place
on the map,

554
00:46:07,874 --> 00:46:09,138
not a way to live.

555
00:46:09,206 --> 00:46:10,037
don't forget that.

556
00:46:12,271 --> 00:46:14,168
a man has to know
his own mind.

557
00:46:19,900 --> 00:46:23,129
you might begin
your own journal.

558
00:46:39,456 --> 00:46:41,286
lebeck,
whispering: crow.

559
00:47:03,708 --> 00:47:04,839
[owl hooting]

560
00:47:20,631 --> 00:47:21,796
[cocks gun]

561
00:47:27,260 --> 00:47:28,191
[door creaking]

562
00:47:28,259 --> 00:47:29,059
[arrow thwaps]

563
00:47:31,091 --> 00:47:32,189
unh!

564
00:47:32,257 --> 00:47:34,488
[arrow thwaps,
baby crying]

565
00:47:40,919 --> 00:47:42,550
[thunder heart woman
screaming]

566
00:47:47,948 --> 00:47:50,112
[baby screaming]

567
00:47:50,181 --> 00:47:52,911
baby! baby!

568
00:47:56,408 --> 00:47:58,205
[thunder heart woman
screaming]

569
00:47:59,905 --> 00:48:03,794

570
00:48:21,794 --> 00:48:24,958
[men chuckling]

571
00:48:55,408 --> 00:48:56,939
buenas dias.

572
00:48:57,007 --> 00:48:58,571
buenas dias.

573
00:48:58,640 --> 00:49:00,138
[speaking spanish]

574
00:49:05,070 --> 00:49:08,032
he says that
we are his prisoners.

575
00:49:12,565 --> 00:49:14,628
tell him that maybe
it escaped his notice

576
00:49:14,698 --> 00:49:17,994
that he's outnumbered
3 to 1.

577
00:49:18,062 --> 00:49:20,524
[speaking spanish]

578
00:49:30,454 --> 00:49:33,717
he said he would arrest us
if there was 1,000 of us.

579
00:49:48,911 --> 00:49:50,608
[speaking spanish]

580
00:49:54,607 --> 00:49:55,570
dismount!

581
00:49:57,271 --> 00:49:58,802
they're gonna take you
to the governor.

582
00:49:58,872 --> 00:50:00,136
all right, fletcher,
you look after the men.

583
00:50:03,901 --> 00:50:05,998
jacob: the captain took
mr. smith away...

584
00:50:06,068 --> 00:50:09,630
"to make the governor's
acquaintance," he said.

585
00:50:09,698 --> 00:50:11,795
under ordinary circumstances,

586
00:50:11,863 --> 00:50:15,626
we might've welcomed
the hospitality of
the san gabriel padres,

587
00:50:15,694 --> 00:50:19,356
but there was no mistaking
the fact that we were prisoners.

588
00:51:08,631 --> 00:51:12,631
jacob: our time among the mohave
was to cost us both dearly.

589
00:50:33,192 --> 00:50:35,175

590
00:50:37,085 --> 00:50:40,182

591
00:50:43,166 --> 00:50:47,986

592
00:50:48,722 --> 00:50:52,769

593
00:50:57,089 --> 00:51:00,202

594
00:51:01,235 --> 00:51:03,369

595
00:51:13,127 --> 00:51:15,758
the soldados wanted
to set an example.

596
00:51:15,825 --> 00:51:18,787
it didn't matter to them
if the men they brought in
as horse thieves

597
00:51:18,857 --> 00:51:21,220
were innocent or guilty.

598
00:51:21,288 --> 00:51:22,485
indians were indians.

599
00:51:40,678 --> 00:51:44,678
it was a powerful trial to watch
the sun set day after day

600
00:51:45,507 --> 00:51:49,303
over the horizon
i had sacrificed
home and family to reach.

601
00:51:49,372 --> 00:51:52,135
whether any of us would live
to see the wide ocean

602
00:51:52,204 --> 00:51:54,400
that had been the object
of our expedition

603
00:51:54,470 --> 00:51:56,434
now depended on mr. smith.

604
00:51:59,732 --> 00:52:00,663
gentlemen.

605
00:52:00,732 --> 00:52:02,064
mr. smith.

606
00:52:02,130 --> 00:52:04,361
gentlemen, gather around.
i got some news for you.

607
00:52:04,429 --> 00:52:05,493
where you been?

608
00:52:05,562 --> 00:52:07,193
the governor has given us

609
00:52:07,261 --> 00:52:09,626
most generous
but strict instructions.

610
00:52:09,693 --> 00:52:13,056
we must depart as we came

611
00:52:13,125 --> 00:52:15,289
and never return
on pain of death.

612
00:52:34,546 --> 00:52:38,546
jacob: we were forced
to return east.

613
00:52:38,777 --> 00:52:40,708
i looked back and made myself
a solemn promise

614
00:52:40,776 --> 00:52:43,872
that one day i would see
california again.

615
00:52:59,770 --> 00:53:01,833
old indian:
loved by the buffalo knew

616
00:53:01,902 --> 00:53:04,033
that a vision
from wakan tanka

617
00:53:04,100 --> 00:53:06,663
would direct
the course of his life.

618
00:53:09,698 --> 00:53:12,293
[drums, chanting continue]

619
00:53:14,595 --> 00:53:16,592
[men whooping]

620
00:53:19,458 --> 00:53:23,389
old indian: white buffalo woman
brought us the sacred ceremonies

621
00:53:23,456 --> 00:53:26,285
so that we could ask for help
in our troubles

622
00:53:26,354 --> 00:53:29,117
and give thanks for the gifts
from wakan tanka.

623
00:53:29,185 --> 00:53:32,115
she taught us the sun dance.

624
00:53:32,183 --> 00:53:34,314
[chanting intensifies]

625
00:54:20,156 --> 00:54:21,722
[blowing whistle]

626
00:54:27,352 --> 00:54:30,514
[tweet]

627
00:54:45,174 --> 00:54:47,571
jacob: once we drank maricopa
with the mohave

628
00:54:47,641 --> 00:54:49,237
and shared their women.

629
00:54:49,305 --> 00:54:52,367
but after we had left them,
a party of beaver-eaters

630
00:54:52,437 --> 00:54:55,167
had attacked their village
and left it in flames.

631
00:54:55,235 --> 00:54:58,297
now we were forced
to run for our lives.

632
00:55:19,187 --> 00:55:20,085
aah!

633
00:55:33,447 --> 00:55:35,777
[gunfire continues]

634
00:55:35,844 --> 00:55:38,174
move. move, jake,
come on.

635
00:55:40,775 --> 00:55:42,706
[mohave whooping]

636
00:55:45,538 --> 00:55:47,635
there. get in.

637
00:55:51,968 --> 00:55:52,931
hurry up.

638
00:56:02,828 --> 00:56:04,459
you ok?

639
00:56:15,887 --> 00:56:16,818
hey, you all right?

640
00:56:26,215 --> 00:56:27,779
fletcher: stay low.

641
00:56:30,380 --> 00:56:31,180
smith: fire!

642
00:56:57,197 --> 00:57:00,226
bully for you, young man.

643
00:57:00,295 --> 00:57:03,324
that should hold 'em off
for a while.

644
00:57:03,394 --> 00:57:04,992
mr. fletcher.

645
00:57:05,057 --> 00:57:06,521
yeah.

646
00:57:06,592 --> 00:57:07,789
the smoke is drifting.

647
00:57:07,857 --> 00:57:09,754
what does that mean?

648
00:57:09,821 --> 00:57:11,252
it means there's
a way out of here.

649
00:57:11,321 --> 00:57:12,152
[coughing]

650
00:57:18,117 --> 00:57:19,748
i got a pang tellin' me

651
00:57:19,817 --> 00:57:21,214
it's time to hang
up the fiddle.

652
00:57:21,282 --> 00:57:24,777
listen, you two just
follow the smoke,

653
00:57:24,847 --> 00:57:27,777
and i'll--i'll keep
our friends amused.

654
00:57:27,845 --> 00:57:31,342
ok? jacob,
bring me my gun.

655
00:57:35,573 --> 00:57:38,570
thank you.

656
00:57:38,639 --> 00:57:39,868
[coughing]

657
00:57:39,938 --> 00:57:40,738
whoa.

658
00:57:45,034 --> 00:57:48,064
listen, jacob,

659
00:57:48,133 --> 00:57:49,830
i want you to have that.

660
00:57:49,900 --> 00:57:51,963
no use a mohave
getting it.

661
00:57:52,031 --> 00:57:54,528
they won't appreciate it.

662
00:57:54,597 --> 00:57:56,193
learn to use it, son.

663
00:57:56,262 --> 00:57:58,857
things can get
pretty personal...

664
00:57:58,927 --> 00:57:59,892
[strained] out west.

665
00:57:59,960 --> 00:58:00,958
thank you, mr. fletcher.

666
00:58:03,525 --> 00:58:05,753
jacob, light!

667
00:58:07,189 --> 00:58:09,086
jim.

668
00:58:09,155 --> 00:58:10,520
yeah.

669
00:58:10,587 --> 00:58:12,151
you're a man of
unfailing rectitude.

670
00:58:13,551 --> 00:58:14,748
remember me...

671
00:58:14,817 --> 00:58:18,013
to all the boys
at the rendezvous.

672
00:58:18,083 --> 00:58:19,214
now get gone.

673
00:58:27,076 --> 00:58:29,707
get gone.

674
00:58:29,775 --> 00:58:30,738
[whooping]

675
00:58:32,807 --> 00:58:34,039
aah!

676
00:58:34,106 --> 00:58:36,037
[gunshot]

677
00:58:36,104 --> 00:58:38,268
[drums continue]

678
00:58:42,235 --> 00:58:43,499
[screeches]

679
00:58:49,664 --> 00:58:53,393
[tweet]

680
00:58:53,461 --> 00:58:55,625
[bird screeches]

681
00:58:58,660 --> 00:59:00,424
[chanting continues]

682
00:59:01,989 --> 00:59:04,818
[tweet]

683
00:59:25,909 --> 00:59:27,439
jacob: mr. smith,
i can't do this.

684
00:59:27,508 --> 00:59:28,738
of course you can.

685
00:59:28,806 --> 00:59:30,272
it vents.

686
00:59:30,339 --> 00:59:32,801
[chanting, drums continue]

687
00:59:46,231 --> 00:59:48,028
[blows whistle]

688
00:59:57,590 --> 01:00:01,553
jacob: now i'm stuck.
now i'm stuck.

689
01:00:01,622 --> 01:00:04,285
i can't do this!
i don't wanna die like this!

690
01:00:04,353 --> 01:00:06,484
oh, god! no!

691
01:00:06,552 --> 01:00:07,616
smith: jacob!

692
01:00:14,646 --> 01:00:16,976
old indian: the dancer
stares into the sun,

693
01:00:17,045 --> 01:00:18,910
sun-up to sundown,

694
01:00:18,978 --> 01:00:20,875
moving with the sun,
dancing,

695
01:00:20,943 --> 01:00:22,407
tugging at his tether,

696
01:00:22,475 --> 01:00:24,039
pulling, twisting,

697
01:00:24,108 --> 01:00:27,038
trying to tear the skewer
through his skin.

698
01:00:29,205 --> 01:00:31,468
and when he sets himself free,

699
01:00:31,537 --> 01:00:33,468
he is reborn to the world.

700
01:00:33,536 --> 01:00:35,998
he lays on a bed of sage

701
01:00:36,068 --> 01:00:38,663
and recites his vision
to the holy man.

702
01:00:40,465 --> 01:00:44,161
jacob: if we never
found this cave,
it would be over.

703
01:00:44,230 --> 01:00:45,726
unh!

704
01:00:45,795 --> 01:00:48,526
but in here like this,
we'll die by inches

705
01:00:48,595 --> 01:00:50,459
and nobody will ever
hear from us again

706
01:00:50,526 --> 01:00:51,755
or know what happened.

707
01:00:53,492 --> 01:00:55,155
the lord revealed the cave

708
01:00:55,223 --> 01:00:58,619
as he sent a fish
to save jonah.

709
01:00:58,688 --> 01:01:00,018
jonah was drowning.

710
01:01:00,087 --> 01:01:02,916
i don't need a sermon
when i'm so afeard!

711
01:01:02,985 --> 01:01:05,315
"the fear of the lord
is the beginning of wisdom."

712
01:01:05,383 --> 01:01:06,947
and take hold my boot,
move with me!

713
01:01:08,781 --> 01:01:10,412
the fish swallowed up jonah.

714
01:01:10,482 --> 01:01:12,611
jonah did not know
it was god

715
01:01:12,679 --> 01:01:14,511
who sent the fish
to save him.

716
01:01:14,579 --> 01:01:15,741
[blows whistle]

717
01:01:15,810 --> 01:01:18,774
and jonah cried out
to the lord

718
01:01:18,842 --> 01:01:20,239
from the belly
of the beast,

719
01:01:20,309 --> 01:01:24,309
"lord, i do not want
to die like this!"

720
01:01:24,539 --> 01:01:26,303
now let us pray
jonah's prayer.

721
01:01:26,371 --> 01:01:28,768
"i cried by reason of mine
affliction unto the lord,

722
01:01:28,836 --> 01:01:30,899
"and he heard me.

723
01:01:30,969 --> 01:01:34,665
out of the belly of hell
cried i and thou
heardest my voice."

724
01:01:34,732 --> 01:01:37,430
now repeat after me,
jacob.

725
01:01:37,498 --> 01:01:39,328
"but i will sacrifice
unto thee..."

726
01:01:39,397 --> 01:01:41,227
jacob: "i will sacrifice
unto thee..."

727
01:01:41,296 --> 01:01:43,160
"with a song
of thanksgiving..."

728
01:01:43,228 --> 01:01:44,758
thanksgiving!

729
01:01:44,828 --> 01:01:47,691
"salvation
is of the lord."

730
01:01:47,758 --> 01:01:49,855
unh! "salvation
is of the lord."

731
01:01:52,523 --> 01:01:54,654
[jacob laughing]

732
01:01:58,053 --> 01:02:00,783
[chanting continues]

733
01:02:19,075 --> 01:02:20,871
[both sighing]

734
01:02:25,104 --> 01:02:27,167
old indian:
loved by the buffalo had seen

735
01:02:27,235 --> 01:02:29,498
how a vision could
kill its seeker.

736
01:02:29,567 --> 01:02:32,663
now he, too, had
a terrible revelation.

737
01:02:36,141 --> 01:02:38,501

738
01:02:39,236 --> 01:02:40,588

739
01:02:41,524 --> 01:02:45,003

740
01:02:45,899 --> 01:02:48,018

741
01:02:49,195 --> 01:02:52,738

742
01:02:55,106 --> 01:02:59,074

743
01:02:59,715 --> 01:03:03,617

744
01:03:04,042 --> 01:03:07,777

745
01:03:13,940 --> 01:03:17,936
the sickness of the spotted face
came to the lakota.

746
01:03:18,004 --> 01:03:20,801
some believed it came
from the white man.

747
01:03:20,869 --> 01:03:22,367
some were not as certain.

748
01:03:24,692 --> 01:03:28,805

749
01:03:31,428 --> 01:03:33,987

750
01:03:37,804 --> 01:03:40,995

751
01:03:42,524 --> 01:03:44,706

752
01:03:43,790 --> 01:03:46,087
when loved by the buffalo
fell ill,

753
01:03:46,155 --> 01:03:48,020
soaring eagle
told the people

754
01:03:48,087 --> 01:03:51,017
it was loved by the buffalo
that brought the pox to them.

755
01:03:51,637 --> 01:03:54,451

756
01:03:57,051 --> 01:04:00,162

757
01:04:02,138 --> 01:04:03,210

758
01:04:03,878 --> 01:04:06,707
he told them
to send the boy away,

759
01:04:06,777 --> 01:04:09,375
and only then would
the sickness leave.

760
01:04:14,772 --> 01:04:16,736
but deep inside
his dark thoughts,

761
01:04:16,803 --> 01:04:19,865
he hoped the sickness
would take the boy.

762
01:04:54,711 --> 01:04:56,648

763
01:05:00,055 --> 01:05:02,196

764
01:05:03,383 --> 01:05:06,086

765
01:05:07,062 --> 01:05:08,589

766
01:05:09,125 --> 01:05:15,940

767
01:05:17,596 --> 01:05:19,972

768
01:05:30,184 --> 01:05:32,345
old indian:
growling bear made a song
to fight the sickness.

769
01:05:32,395 --> 01:05:33,750
he gave it to
loved by the buffalo

770
01:05:33,798 --> 01:05:36,388
to cure his brother running fox
and any who believed.

771
01:06:20,000 --> 01:06:21,306
mr. smith and i

772
01:06:21,355 --> 01:06:25,355
had stared death in the face
and lived to tell the tale.

773
01:06:25,827 --> 01:06:28,203
we'd said our good-byes
and gone our separate ways.

774
01:06:28,253 --> 01:06:29,820
so i decided to attend
the rendezvous

775
01:06:29,870 --> 01:06:31,201
that mr. fletcher
had spoken of
with such fondness.

776
01:07:30,000 --> 01:07:32,846
rob any
chicken coops lately?

777
01:07:32,915 --> 01:07:34,730
ben franklin.

778
01:07:34,802 --> 01:07:36,962
jacob wheeler!
ain't this some pumpkins!

779
01:07:37,032 --> 01:07:38,470
look at ya!

780
01:07:38,539 --> 01:07:40,560
look at you!
where in the sam hill
you been?

781
01:07:40,635 --> 01:07:43,480
i been all over.
ha ha! come here!

782
01:07:43,548 --> 01:07:45,226
ha ha ha!

783
01:07:45,301 --> 01:07:46,633
i remember.
i remember.

784
01:07:46,705 --> 01:07:48,349
i never forget that.

785
01:07:48,422 --> 01:07:50,819
i been treed
by grizzly bears and
tracked by blackfeet,

786
01:07:50,893 --> 01:07:52,672
but i never
was so scared

787
01:07:52,744 --> 01:07:54,732
as when i heard
that farmer tell you
about a reward

788
01:07:54,801 --> 01:07:57,613
for a runaway slave.
no, sir! ha ha!

789
01:07:57,685 --> 01:08:01,685
i sat in that coop
waitin' for you
to give me up.

790
01:08:01,905 --> 01:08:04,887
mm. sho' enough...

791
